One of the leading aspirants for the national chairmanship of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Senator Sani Musa, has said he is sure President Muhammadu Buhari will not support imposition of any candidate against the popular will of the majority. The aspirant, who currently represents Niger East in the National Assembly, has been speaking on his programmes while consulting party stakeholders across the country ahead of the party’s convention.   CECPC divided over Niger gov’s alleged plan to summon NEC     Accept my leadership or quit, Obaseki tells Edo PDP leaders     IPOB takes on enforcers of Monday sit-at-home   “We believe in the leadership of President Muhammadu Buhari. The President, being a democrat, will never subscribe to imposition against the will of majority party faithful. Hence, we shall continue our consultations and prepare ourselves for the national convention with the hope of winning the national chairmanship contest. “Furthermore, as genuine party faithful, we will always be open to abide by any genuine consideration with superior reasoning, if brokered by Mr. President, in return for a consensus arrangement. This cannot be pushed away and in a manner like what is being peddled now as an endorsement of a non-prepared individual as one,” he said.